			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Dreadblaze wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Assuming a new Mage progressing upwards from a totally non-twink state...what level is it feasible to first start efficiently doing pet canni?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Absolute minimum requirement for pet cannibalisation:
<br />

<br />
lv 49 earth pet
<br />

<br />
the spell reclaim energy
<br />

<br />
You will get mana back, but it will take time and cost a lot of malachites.
<br />

<br />
Easily obtainable tools that makes cannipetting more efficient:
<br />

<br />
Sol Ro focus items has right click, instant cast reclaim energy. Speeds things up and because they can be used from the inventory, they save a spell slot too.
<br />

<br />
Summoning haste III item. Makes the cycles go faster.
<br />

<br />
Summoning efficiency III item. Makes you use less mana when you summon a pet.
<br />

<br />
Specialise conjuration helps, but cannipetting is also efficient for a specialise evocation magician. Having no summoning efficiency III item makes cannipetting almost useless if you are specialise evocation.
<br />

<br />
Having the AA-skills quick summoning at some level helps. Higher level helps more, but it is easy to hit the spell haste cap.
<br />

<br />
Elemental pact makes you use no malachites when you summon a pet, but you still need to carry at least one malachite. Rathes son use no malachite to summon, so once you get that pet, elemental pact becomes redundant (in regard to cannipetting). Ward of Xegony still use malachites if you have no elemental pact.
<br />

<br />
One of the high level pet focus items also help with the efficiency of cannipetting.
<br />

<br />
nmee<br />_________________<br /><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">Nmee Lightarch</A>
<br />
Prestidigitator
<br />
<A href="http://www.povartarewalliance.org/">Povar Tarew Alliance</A></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
